==== 關於時尚 ====
2002年，拉格斐問到[[迪賽|迪賽]]的創立人[[倫佐·羅索|倫佐·羅索]]，合作為拉格斐畫廊（Lagerfeld Gallery）推出特別的牛仔布系列作品<ref>Tungate, Mark: "Fifty". Gestalten Verlag; 2005. {{ISBN|978-3-89955-095-5}}</ref>。該拉格斐畫廊系列由迪賽負責，是由拉格斐共同設計，然後由迪賽的創意團隊在羅索的監督下發展下去。它包括了在[[巴黎時裝週|巴黎時裝週]]期間，設計師的時裝表演所展出的五件作品<ref name="pop">{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2002/05/10/pop-goes-the-diesel |title=Pop Goes the Diesel |date=2002-05-10 |work=Vogue |access-date=2011-10-24 |archive-date=2012-02-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120208145259/http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2002/05/10/pop-goes-the-diesel |dead-url=no }}</ref>。那些展品分別於巴黎及[[摩納哥|摩納哥]]的拉格斐畫廊，以及紐約和東京的迪賽牛仔布畫廊（Diesel Denim Gallery）以高價限量版出售。在紐約銷售的第一周，儘管價格從$240美元至$1,840美元不等，超過90％的褲子已經售罄<ref>{{cite web |first=Jenny |last=Bailly |url=http://www.fashionwindows.com/beauty/diesel/experimental.asp |title=Diesel Gets 'Experimental' As Lagerfeld Gallery Takes Soho Store by Storm |publisher=Fashionwindows.com |date=2002-08-09 |access-date=2011-11-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131027084355/http://www.fashionwindows.com/beauty/diesel/experimental.asp |archivedate=2013-10-27 }}</ref>。在巴黎演出後的一份聲明中，羅索說：「我很榮幸能夠遇到我們這個時代的時尚偶像。卡爾代表著創造力，傳統和挑戰，而事實上他認為跟迪賽合作是一份很好的禮物，並承認我們作為休閒服裝的[[成衣|prêt-à-porter]]<ref name="pop" />。」

2006年12月，拉格斐宣布推出一個新系列的男裝和女裝，名為「K Karl Lagerfeld」，當中包括合身的T恤和各種牛仔褲<ref>{{cite web |url=http://designer.denim.in.th/article.php/Karl-Lagerfeld-Launches-Denim-Collection |title=Karl Lagerfeld Launches New Denim Collection |publisher=Designer Denim News |date=2007-01-01 |access-date=2011-09-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110814132313/http://designer.denim.in.th/article.php/Karl-Lagerfeld-Launches-Denim-Collection |archivedate=2011-08-14 }}</ref>。

2010年9月，在紐約市[[大衛·格芬廳|大衛·格芬廳]]的籌款午宴上，{{le|科技時裝學院|Fashion Institute of Technology}}的時裝委員會博物館（Couture Council of The Museum）以拉格斐的名義設立一個獎項—「時裝委員會會時尚遠見獎（The Couture Council Fashion Visionary Award）」<ref>{{cite web |title=2010 Couture Council Fashion Visionary Award: Karl Lagerfeld |url=http://www.fitnyc.edu/8693.asp |work=Museum at FIT |access-date=2011-09-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110828174730/http://www.fitnyc.edu/8693.asp |archivedate=2011-08-28 }}</ref>。2010年11月，拉格斐與瑞典水晶製造商{{le|奧弗可斯水晶|Orrefors glassworks}}宣布合作設計水晶藝術品系列<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scandinaviandesign.com/orrefors/2010/101110.htm |title=Orrefors och Karl Lagerfeldt inleder designsamarbete |publisher=Orrefors |date=2010-11-10 |access-date=2011-09-08 |archive-date=2011-11-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111109053445/http://scandinaviandesign.com/orrefors/2010/101110.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。首個系列於2011年春季推出，該系列稱為「拉格斐的奧弗可斯水晶」<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2011/06/08/karl-lagerfeld-glassware-collection-for-orrefors |title=Raise A Glass |first=Lauren |last=Milligan |date=2011-06-08 |newspaper=Vogue |access-date=2011-09-08 |archive-date=2011-09-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110903051401/http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2011/06/08/karl-lagerfeld-glassware-collection-for-orrefors |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2014年，佛羅里達州的一家拍賣行宣布，有許多拉格斐為羅馬提西亞尼之家（House of Tiziani）的早期草圖將會被出售<ref>{{cite news |title=Karl Lagerfeld's early fashion sketches to be auctioned |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/karl-lagerfelds-early-fashion-sketches-668213 |publisher=Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=2019-02-25 |archive-date=2019-03-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329183806/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/karl-lagerfelds-early-fashion-sketches-668213 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Bergin |first=Olivia |title=Early sketches by Karl Lagerfeld go up for auction in Florida |url=http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/article/TMG10546695/Early-sketches-by-Karl-Lagerfeld-go-up-for-auction-in-Florida.html |publisher=Telegraph |location=London |date=2014-01-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104010032/http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/article/TMG10546695/Early-sketches-by-Karl-Lagerfeld-go-up-for-auction-in-Florida.html |archivedate=2014-01-04 |accessdate=2019-02-25 }}</ref>。

